{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Ibn Majah","section":{"36":{"eng-name":"Tribulations","ara-name":"كتاب الفتن"}},"section_detail":{"36":{"hadithnumber_first":3927,"hadithnumber_last":4099,"arabicnumber_first":3927,"arabicnumber_last":4099}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":3938,"arabicnumber":3938,"text":"It was narrated that Tha’labah bin Hakam said:“We came across some of the enemy’s sheep and plundered them, and set up our cooking pots. The Prophet (ﷺ) passed by the pots and ordered that they be overturned, then he said: ‘Plunder is not permissible.’”","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Hasan"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Isnaad Hasan"}],"reference":{"book":36,"hadith":13},"chapter":{"id":3,"ara-name":"باب النَّهْىِ عَنِ النُّهْبَةِ","eng-name":"The prohibition of plunder","isFirstHadith":false}}]}